The original content (tutorials, guides, courses, and media) was created by
IBM and the Qiskit community. doQumentation adds an open-source web frontend
with live code execution, translations, and offline deployment capabilities.

Upstream content is tracked as a git submodule (upstream-docs/) pointing to a
fork (https://github.com/JanLahmann/Qiskit-documentation) which is periodically
synced from the original Qiskit/documentation repository. The fork adds a custom
hello-world tutorial; all other content originates from IBM's repository.

This project includes tutorial content from Qiskit Addon repositories
(all licensed under Apache License 2.0, Copyright IBM Corp.):
  https://github.com/Qiskit/qiskit-addon-cutting
  https://github.com/Qiskit/qiskit-addon-sqd
  https://github.com/Qiskit/qiskit-addon-obp
  https://github.com/Qiskit/qiskit-addon-mpf
  https://github.com/Qiskit/qiskit-addon-aqc-tensor
  https://github.com/Qiskit/qiskit-addon-pna
  https://github.com/Qiskit/qiskit-addon-slc
Addon tutorials are tracked as git submodules in upstream-addons/.

Jupyter dependency lists (binder/jupyter-requirements*.txt) are derived from the
upstream repository's scripts/nb-tester/requirements.txt (Apache 2.0).

The /qamposer page embeds the QAMPoser visual quantum circuit composer:
  https://github.com/QAMP-62/qamposer-react
  https://github.com/QAMP-62/qamposer-backend
  Copyright 2024-2026 QAMP-62 contributors
  Licensed under Apache License 2.0
The React component (@qamposer/react) is used as an npm dependency.
The Python simulation + Q-sphere logic in
src/components/QamposerEmbed/thebelabAdapter.ts is a line-by-line port of
qamposer-backend's src/backend/quantum/{simulator,converter,qsphere}.py —
kept inline so it runs inside doQumentation's existing thebelab kernel
and honors the user's doQumentation Settings (ideal / noisy fake / real
IBM Quantum). A future release will replace the inline port with a pip
package derived from qamposer-backend.

